            <title>[THRIFT-3279] Fix a bug in retry_max_delay (NodeJS)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3279</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current max delay is unstable - when retry_delay == retry_max_delay the second branch is taken, and retry_delay is set to retry_max_delay * retry_backoff, which is larger than retry_max_delay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This causes an oscillation between retry_max_delay and retry_max_delay * retry_backoff.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
